                          --- About Astrokid ---

Astrokid has previously been released under the name 'Calvin and Hobbes -
Goes for the Gusto', but due to copyright restrictions it couldn't be
distributed via Aminet. So it was totally rewritten and the graphics were
redone.
	The game is a mix of all sorts of game types, and the different chapters
(the same as levels or stages in other games, but I felt 'chapters' was
better for this game) vary greatly in quality, from fairly boring over quite
puzzling to extremely stimulating. For info about the different levels,
check out the built-in instruction manual in the game.
	If I get a lot of response from people (YOU!!!) I may continue the
develpment of the game, elsehow it may strand on the current level (It's up
to you!)

           --- Installing to HD or making a bootable Floppy ---

Installation to harddisk is very simple, just unpack the .lha archive
to the prefered drawer, and run the game.
	Making a bootable floppy is done by formatting a disk (use Workbench),
and to make it bootable put the disk into the disk drive and write 'Install
DF0:' in the cli. Then unpack the .lha archive to the floppy (it should fit
with a few Kbs extra). Now you have a bootable gamedisk :)


                     --- How to get the most of it ---

If you wan't to achieve the best possible colours, then use the following
direction lines:
If you are using a Philips CM8833(-II) or a Commodore 1084(S) monitor
you should turn the contrast button to maximum and the brightness button to
a little below average. If you are using a TV turn the brightness to very
low and the contrast to a little above average.
If you are using a multisync monitor or a VGA monitor, I don't even know if
the game will run :)

To achieve best possible speed you should boot the game from floppy disk,
or close all other applictions before running it. Alternatively you could
(if you are using an Amiga with 2.0 or better kickstart, with harddisk)
reset the computer, and select 'boot with no startup-sequence' from the
early startup-sequence, and then run the game as the first thing after
this.


