                         --- Testing Equipment ---

At present the game has been tested on an A1200 2mb chip, A600 1mb chip and
1mb fast, and an A500 1/2mb chip and 1/2mb fast. And was running smoothly
(except chapter 4 (the caves) which takes a 68020+ to avoid jerky scroll).

It has even been run on a 90mhz Pentium with 32mb of memory, and NetBSD as
operating system, using an Amiga emulator and a 3.0 kickstart, the only bug
was that some colours were f**ked up a bit. Cooool ;>

May not work with VGA monitors? (I don't know if AMOS support these?)


